'''Land assault troopers''', also known as '''Imperial Army assault troopers''', were [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]] deployed with surface attack vehicles and trained to operate a variety of land war machines. Several land assault troopers were stationed aboard the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star]].

==Description==
Land assault troopers could serve two separate but complimentary roles within the [[Imperial Army/Legends|Imperial Army]], the first of which was as mechanized [[Infantry/Legends|infantry]]. While given all the training of normal [[Imperial Army trooper/Legends|Imperial Army troopers]], particular attention was made towards the advantages and limitations of mechanized combat vehicles. Their training in vehicle repair and operation allowed these troopers to fulfill the second role of crewing ground vehicles, whether as drivers, [[Gunner/Legends|gunners]] or [[Commander/Legends|commanders]].<ref name="IE">[[Imperial Entanglements (Star Wars Miniatures Battles)|''Imperial Entanglements'']]</ref><ref name="DSTC">''[[Death Star Technical Companion]]''</ref>

Land assault troopers wore impact-absorbing uniforms, partial body [[Armor/Legends|armor]] and [[Sensor/Legends|sensor]]-equipped helmets, along with carrying environmental gear.<ref name="DSTC" /> The lenses in their helmets varied, with a number of different tinted and vision-enhancing versions in use by the army.<ref name="IE" />

Imperial Army assault troopers were often carried into battle aboard [[All Terrain Armored Transport/Legends|All Terrain Armored Transports]].<ref name="TEFTWAT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The picture of the Imperial land assault trooper is based on unused concept art from [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']] of a vehicle pilot and first featured in the ''[[Death Star Technical Companion]]'', along with a short description of their role. They again appeared in [[Imperial Entanglements (Star Wars Miniatures Battles)|''Imperial Entanglements'']], with game statistics and equipment listed for their use in the ''[[Star Wars Miniatures]]''. However, in the ''[[Imperial Sourcebook]]'' the term Assault Trooper is used to describe [[Vehicle Command Crewer|Imperial Army pilots]].

The land assault trooper is not to be confused with the [[assault trooper]], a variant of the [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]].

